The paper deals with the problem of subgraph isomorphism in planar graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and graph theory. The techniques used in the paper involve graph decomposition and dynamic programming, which are common in the areas of data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also presents an algorithmic improvement for the problem, which is relevant to the subfield of algorithms and complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG) as subgraph isomorphism is a common problem in graph-based machine learning applications.
